snippet.textDisplay: If you buy a new candle and want to burn it like the one on you’re countertop just put a tablespoon of normal salt in warm water and put the candle in there over night but keep the top of the candle and the wick out of the water. snippet.textDisplay: Good rule of thumb for hanging artwork is to hang at gallery height.  Measure from the floor to the center of the art piece to 60” (normal eye level).  If above a sofa or piece of furniture, the bottom of the art piece should be 6” or 8” from top of sofa.    And always think in odd numbers.  3 or 5 is always better than an even number.  More pleasing to the eye.  Lovely home.
snippet.textOriginal: Good rule of thumb for hanging artwork is to hang at gallery height.  Measure from the floor to the center of the art piece to 60” (normal eye level).  If above a sofa or piece of furniture, the bottom of the art piece should be 6” or 8” from top of sofa.    And always think in odd numbers.  3 or 5 is always better than an even number.
